        <heading>541.  Divisibility of usufruct</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 541.  Divisibility of usufruct.
Usufruct is susceptible to division, because its purpose is the enjoyment of advantages that are themselves divisible.  It may be conferred on several persons in divided or undivided shares, and it may be partitioned among the usufructuaries.</p>
        </content>
